+              <div className="pt-2">
+                <label className={labelClass}>Global Default Font</label>
+                <select name="default_font" value={localSettings.default_font || 'arial.ttf'} onChange={(e) => setLocalSettings({ ...localSettings, default_font: e.target.value })} className={inputClass}>
+                  <option value="arial.ttf">System Arial</option>
+                  {fonts.map(f => (
+                    <option key={f.id} value={f.name}>{f.name.split('.')[0]}</option>
+                  ))}
+                </select>
+                <p className="text-[9px] text-neutral-400 mt-1">Applies to all newly created text items.</p>
+              </div>
+            </div>
+```
+
+#### 6. Renderer Engine Reliability Fallback
+*File: `backend/template.py`*
+Ensure if an agent submits a payload without a font specified at all, we fallback to Arial so the script doesn't crash.
+
+```python
+# --- backend/template.py ---
+# Ensure item_type == "text" and "icon_text" handles missing fonts gracefully.
+# You've already got this mostly covered with `item.get("font", "arial.ttf")`, 
+# but it's good to ensure it's explicitly set. No changes strictly needed in template.py 
+# if item.get("font", "arial.ttf") is already present, but verify this block:
+
+            font_name = item.get("font", "arial.ttf")
+            def get_font(f_size):
+                local_font_path = os.path.join("fonts", font_name)
+                if os.path.exists(local_font_path):
+                    return ImageFont.truetype(local_font_path, int(f_size))
+                try:
+                    return ImageFont.truetype(font_name, int(f_size))
+                except IOError:
+                    return ImageFont.load_default()
+```
+*(No action needed in `template.py`, just pointing out that agents omitting the `"font"` key will default cleanly to standard Arial).*

