# 2026-04-09 22:44:19.311518
+Please implement this: This is an excellent feature request. Because you are building a tool specifically for **thermal label printers and batch processing**, the architectural choice here is crucial.
+
+### Architectural Evaluation: JS vs. Python QR Generation
+
+**Option 1: Pure Frontend (JS Library like `qrcode`)**
+*   **Pros:** Real-time, pixel-perfect preview in the browser. 
+*   **Cons:** It breaks your batch printing engine. If the frontend generates a static Base64 image and sends it to the backend, the backend cannot inject dynamic variables (e.g., `{{ order_id }}`) into the QR code data during a batch data stream. 
+
+**Option 2: Pure Backend (Python `qrcode` library)**
+*   **Pros:** Perfect integration with your batching engine. The backend can iterate over a CSV, inject variables into the QR data, and generate unique QR codes on the fly. No new Node dependencies required.
+*   **Cons:** The frontend canvas cannot show the *exact* QR code pattern live. It will only show a bounding box/placeholder.
+
+**Option 3: Hybrid (Best Approach)**
+*   **Architecture:** Rely strictly on the **Python backend for the actual print rendering** to preserve your variable replacement engine. On the **React frontend, use a semantic placeholder** (e.g., a stylized gray box) for layout purposes. *(Note: You can add a JS library later strictly for the canvas preview, but a placeholder perfectly aligns with how your Barcodes are currently handled and keeps the app lightweight and offline-capable).*
+
+### The Hidden Trap: Thermal Resampling
+Surprisingly, your backend `template.py` *already has* the `qrcode` library installed and handles the `"qrcode"` type! However, it contains a critical flaw: it uses default Pillow image resizing. Standard resizing applies anti-aliasing (blurring) to images, which thermal printers will attempt to dither. **Dithered QR codes are unreadable by scanners.** We must force `NEAREST` neighbor resampling to keep the pixels perfectly crisp.
+
+Here are the exact changes needed to enable QR codes across your stack.
+
+---
+
+### 1. Backend Fix (Fixing blurry QR codes)
+Update your image resizing logic in `template.py` to use `NEAREST` resampling for both QR codes and Barcodes to prevent thermal dithering artifacts.
+
+**File: `timiniprint/rendering/template.py`**
+```python
+<<<<
+        elif item_type == "barcode":
+            data = item.get("data", "")
+            for k, v in variables.items():
+                data = data.replace(f"{{{{ {k} }}}}", str(v))
+                data = data.replace(f"{{{{{k}}}}}", str(v))
+                
+            bclass = barcode.get_barcode_class(item.get("barcode_type", "code128"))
+            writer = ImageWriter()
+            writer.set_options({'write_text': False, 'module_height': 10.0, 'quiet_zone': 1.0})
+            bcode = bclass(data, writer=writer)
+            
+            fp = BytesIO()
+            bcode.write(fp)
+            fp.seek(0)
+            bc_img = Image.open(fp).convert("RGBA")
+            
+            bw = int(item.get("width", bc_img.width))
+            bh = int(item.get("height", bc_img.height))
+            bc_img = bc_img.resize((bw, bh))
+            
+            img.paste(bc_img, (x, y), bc_img)
+            actual_drawn_height = bh
+            
+        elif item_type == "qrcode":
+            data = item.get("data", "")
+            for k, v in variables.items():
+                data = data.replace(f"{{{{ {k} }}}}", str(v))
+                data = data.replace(f"{{{{{k}}}}}", str(v))
+                
+            qr = qrcode.QRCode(box_size=item.get("box_size", 10), border=item.get("border", 1))
+            qr.add_data(data)
+            qr.make(fit=True)
+            qr_img = qr.make_image(fill_color="black", back_color="white").convert("RGBA")
+            
+            bw = int(item.get("width", qr_img.width))
+            bh = int(item.get("height", qr_img.height))
+            qr_img = qr_img.resize((bw, bh))
+            
+            img.paste(qr_img, (x, y), qr_img)
+            actual_drawn_height = bh
+====
+        elif item_type == "barcode":
+            data = item.get("data", "")
+            for k, v in variables.items():
+                data = data.replace(f"{{{{ {k} }}}}", str(v))
+                data = data.replace(f"{{{{{k}}}}}", str(v))
+                
+            bclass = barcode.get_barcode_class(item.get("barcode_type", "code128"))
+            writer = ImageWriter()
+            writer.set_options({'write_text': False, 'module_height': 10.0, 'quiet_zone': 1.0})
+            bcode = bclass(data, writer=writer)
+            
+            fp = BytesIO()
+            bcode.write(fp)
+            fp.seek(0)
+            bc_img = Image.open(fp).convert("RGBA")
+            
+            bw = int(item.get("width", bc_img.width))
+            bh = int(item.get("height", bc_img.height))
+            # CRITICAL: Use NEAREST to prevent anti-aliasing which breaks thermal dithering
+            bc_img = bc_img.resize((bw, bh), Image.Resampling.NEAREST)
+            
+            img.paste(bc_img, (x, y), bc_img)
+            actual_drawn_height = bh
+            
+        elif item_type == "qrcode":
+            data = item.get("data", "")
+            for k, v in variables.items():
+                data = data.replace(f"{{{{ {k} }}}}", str(v))
+                data = data.replace(f"{{{{{k}}}}}", str(v))
+                
+            qr = qrcode.QRCode(box_size=item.get("box_size", 10), border=item.get("border", 1))
+            qr.add_data(data)
+            qr.make(fit=True)
+            qr_img = qr.make_image(fill_color="black", back_color="white").convert("RGBA")
+            
+            bw = int(item.get("width", qr_img.width))
+            bh = int(item.get("height", qr_img.height))
+            # CRITICAL: Use NEAREST to prevent anti-aliasing which breaks thermal dithering
+            qr_img = qr_img.resize((bw, bh), Image.Resampling.NEAREST)
+            
+            img.paste(qr_img, (x, y), qr_img)
+            actual_drawn_height = bh
