# 2026-04-10 03:40:16.296465
+Please implement this: This is an excellent and highly robust approach. By using Micromamba as a portable bootstrapper, we achieve the holy grail of local deployments: **zero system pollution, perfect isolation, and native hardware access** (which is critical for Bluetooth). 
+
+Here is the step-by-step simulation of how `run.sh` / `run.bat` will execute:
+1. **First Execution:** It detects that `./env` is missing. It downloads the standalone `micromamba` binary into `./bin/`. It uses it to create a local environment containing Python 3.11 and Node.js. It installs the backend dependencies via `pip`, the frontend dependencies via `npm`, and builds the React app into optimized static files (`frontend/dist`). Finally, it starts the Python server.
+2. **Subsequent Executions:** It detects `./env`, skips the entire installation process, and instantly starts the Python server. 
+3. **The Server:** The Python backend acts as a single unified server, handling API requests, serving the SQLite database from `./data/`, and serving the compiled frontend UI on the root (`/`) path.
+
+Here are the exact changes required to implement this.
+
+### 1. New Files (The Bootstrappers & Gitignore)
+
+Create **`run.sh`** (For macOS / Linux):
+```bash
+#!/bin/bash
+set -e
+
+echo "=== TiMini Print Bootstrapper ==="
+
+if [ ! -d "env" ]; then
+    echo "[1/4] Environment not found. Starting installation..."
+    
+    mkdir -p bin data
+    if [ ! -f "bin/micromamba" ]; then
+        echo "      Downloading standalone Micromamba..."
+        OS="$(uname -s | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')"
+        ARCH="$(uname -m)"
+        if [ "$ARCH" = "x86_64" ]; then ARCH="64"; fi
+        if [ "$ARCH" = "aarch64" ]; then ARCH="aarch64"; fi
+        if [ "$ARCH" = "arm64" ]; then ARCH="arm64"; fi
+        
+        # Download and extract just the binary directly into ./bin/
+        curl -Ls "https://micro.mamba.pm/api/micromamba/${OS}-${ARCH}/latest" | tar -xvj -C bin bin/micromamba --strip-components=1
+    fi
+
+    echo "[2/4] Creating isolated environment (Python & Node.js)..."
+    ./bin/micromamba create -p ./env -c conda-forge python=3.11 nodejs -y
+
+    echo "[3/4] Installing backend dependencies..."
+    ./bin/micromamba run -p ./env pip install -r requirements.txt
+
+    echo "[4/4] Building optimized frontend UI..."
+    cd frontend
+    ../bin/micromamba run -p ../env npm install
+    ../bin/micromamba run -p ../env npm run build
+    cd ..
+
+    echo "Installation complete!"
+    echo "-----------------------------------"
+fi
+
+echo "Starting TiMini Print Server (http://localhost:8000)..."
+./bin/micromamba run -p ./env python -m timiniprint
+```
+*(Make sure to run `chmod +x run.sh` after creating it).*
+
+Create **`run.bat`** (For Windows):
+```bat
+@echo off
+setlocal
+echo === TiMini Print Bootstrapper ===
+
+if not exist "env\" (
+    echo [1/4] Environment not found. Starting installation...
+
+    if not exist "bin\micromamba.exe" (
+        echo       Downloading standalone Micromamba...
+        mkdir bin 2>nul
+        mkdir data 2>nul
+        curl -L -o bin\micromamba.tar.bz2 "https://micro.mamba.pm/api/micromamba/win-64/latest"
+        REM Windows 10+ has a built in tar command
+        tar -xf bin\micromamba.tar.bz2 -C bin Library/bin/micromamba.exe
+        move /Y bin\Library\bin\micromamba.exe bin\micromamba.exe >nul
+        rmdir /S /Q bin\Library 2>nul
+        del /Q bin\micromamba.tar.bz2 2>nul
+    )
+
+    echo [2/4] Creating isolated environment ^(Python ^& Node.js^)...
+    bin\micromamba.exe create -p .\env -c conda-forge python=3.11 nodejs -y
+
+    echo [3/4] Installing backend dependencies...
+    bin\micromamba.exe run -p .\env pip install -r requirements.txt
+
+    echo [4/4] Building optimized frontend UI...
+    cd frontend
+    ..\bin\micromamba.exe run -p ..\env npm install
+    ..\bin\micromamba.exe run -p ..\env npm run build
+    cd ..
+
+    echo Installation complete!
+    echo -----------------------------------
+)
+
+echo Starting TiMini Print Server (http://localhost:8000)...
+bin\micromamba.exe run -p .\env python -m timiniprint
+```
+
+Create **`.gitignore`** in the root:
+```text
+# Environments and Binaries
+/env/
+/bin/
+
+# User Data
+/data/
+
+# Frontend builds and modules
+/frontend/node_modules/
+/frontend/dist/
+
+# Python
+__pycache__/
+*.py[cod]
+*$py.class
+*.so
+.Python
+build/
+develop-eggs/
+dist/
+downloads/
+eggs/
+.eggs/
+lib/
+lib64/
+parts/
+sdist/
+var/
+wheels/
+*.egg-info/
+.installed.cfg
+*.egg
+
+# OS Files
+.DS_Store
+Thumbs.db
+```
+
+*(You can now safely delete the old `install.bat`, `install.sh`, `start.bat`, and `start.sh`)*
+
+---
+
+### 2. Backend Modifications (`server.py`)
+We need to map the database and fonts to the `./data/` folder, and mount the built React frontend at `/`.
+
+**`timiniprint/app/server.py`:**
+```python
+# ... existing imports ...
+from fastapi.staticfiles import StaticFiles
+# ... existing imports ...
+
+# CHANGE 1: Route database to the data folder
+os.makedirs("data", exist_ok=True)
+sqlite_file_name = "data/timiniprint.db"
+sqlite_url = f"sqlite:///{sqlite_file_name}"
+engine = create_engine(sqlite_url, echo=False)
+
+# ...
+
+# CHANGE 2: Route fonts to the data folder
+os.makedirs("data/fonts", exist_ok=True)
+app.mount("/fonts", StaticFiles(directory="data/fonts"), name="fonts")
+
+# ... (down to the @app.post("/api/fonts") route) ...
+
+@app.post("/api/fonts")
+async def upload_font(file: UploadFile = File(...)):
+    os.makedirs("data/fonts", exist_ok=True)
+    # CHANGE 3: Save to data/fonts
+    file_path = f"data/fonts/{file.filename}"
+    with open(file_path, "wb") as buffer:
+        shutil.copyfileobj(file.file, buffer)
+        
+    with Session(engine) as session:
+        # Keep URL path as fonts/ in DB so the frontend resolves it correctly
+        db_font = Font(name=file.filename, file_path=f"fonts/{file.filename}")
+        session.add(db_font)
+# ...
+
+# ... (down to the @app.get("/api/fonts") route) ...
+
+@app.get("/api/fonts")
+def list_fonts():
+    os.makedirs("data/fonts", exist_ok=True)
+    with Session(engine) as session:
+        db_fonts = {f.name: f for f in session.exec(select(Font)).all()}
+        
+        # CHANGE 4: Read from data/fonts
+        disk_fonts = [f for f in os.listdir("data/fonts") if f.lower().endswith((".ttf", ".otf"))]
+        
+        new_fonts = []
+        for f in disk_fonts:
+            if f not in db_fonts:
+                # Keep URL path as fonts/ in DB
+                new_font = Font(name=f, file_path=f"fonts/{f}")
+                session.add(new_font)
+# ...
+
+# CHANGE 5: Add this right at the VERY BOTTOM of server.py
+# Mount the compiled frontend to the root path. 
+# (Must be at the bottom so it doesn't intercept /api/ routes)
+if os.path.exists("frontend/dist"):
+    app.mount("/", StaticFiles(directory="frontend/dist", html=True), name="frontend")
+```
+
+---
+
